    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "interesting. so you're saying it's a pretty settled fact that the benefits are the main cause? i've seen some people argue that things like automation or just changing demographics are the real reasons the numbers are shifting. wouldn't those be bigger factors than just the welfare programs?",
